# -*- encoding: utf-8 -*-
# Arc: MagePath | Scene: MagePath6
# Source: C:\Program Files (x86)\Steam\steamapps\common\The Survival of Sarah Rose\game\script.rpy

translate ru strings:

    old "Months turned to years as Sarah followed her studies under Xan."
    new "Months turned to years as Sarah followed her studies under Xan."

    old "Her mastery of magic continued to grow as she devoured the endless libraries of the world."
    new "Her mastery of magic continued to grow as she devoured the endless libraries of the world."

    old "The world."
    new "The world."

    old "She had come to see so much of it by now."
    new "She had come to see so much of it by now."

    old "Sarah walked with Xan across every continent and every nation."
    new "Sarah walked with Xan across every continent and every nation."

    old "She came to see places and peoples that had once only been faint stories in her history books."
    new "She came to see places and peoples that had once only been faint stories in her history books."

    old "With every passing year, it surprised Sarah that Xan still seemed so distant to her. So much of the mage was still a mystery."
    new "With every passing year, it surprised Sarah that Xan still seemed so distant to her. So much of the mage was still a mystery."

    old "He allowed her to come with him on his travels, and she helped him do his bidding, but Sarah only ever saw fragments of a design."
    new "He allowed her to come with him on his travels, and she helped him do his bidding, but Sarah only ever saw fragments of a design."

    old "Promises were made, influence was peddled, bribes were handed out."
    new "Promises were made, influence was peddled, bribes were handed out."

    old "Sarah could see they were working towards something, yet she did not know what, nor did Xan ever tell her much of it."
    new "Sarah could see they were working towards something, yet she did not know what, nor did Xan ever tell her much of it."

    old "There was a loneliness in that house, made worse by how Xan kept her at a distance."
    new "There was a loneliness in that house, made worse by how Xan kept her at a distance."

    old "Perhaps it was this fact that drove Sarah into the arms of the spirit."
    new "Perhaps it was this fact that drove Sarah into the arms of the spirit."

    old "She feared the spirit too much to visit it more than every few months, but sooner or later, her urges would overtake her better judgement, and she would meet with the spirit."
    new "She feared the spirit too much to visit it more than every few months, but sooner or later, her urges would overtake her better judgement, and she would meet with the spirit."

    old "An unusual friend in an otherwise lonely place."
    new "An unusual friend in an otherwise lonely place."

    old "The spirit, Razaphel, continued to be an odd presence. It whispered as she passed it, but she ignored the creature as best she could."
    new "The spirit, Razaphel, continued to be an odd presence. It whispered as she passed it, but she ignored the creature as best she could."

    old "Even now, she did not know what to make of the creature."
    new "Even now, she did not know what to make of the creature."

    old "It was under this same set of unclear circumstances that Sarah now found herself in the great palace of the city of Bagrad."
    new "It was under this same set of unclear circumstances that Sarah now found herself in the great palace of the city of Bagrad."

    old "Bagrad had once been a great city. Seated at the heart of a great empire, the city grew so impressive that for centuries after all other cities appeared only poor imitations."
    new "Bagrad had once been a great city. Seated at the heart of a great empire, the city grew so impressive that for centuries after all other cities appeared only poor imitations."

    old "But that had been centuries ago."
    new "But that had been centuries ago."

    old "Today, Bagrad was the last vestige of that old empire. A city that once housed millions; now barely a hundred-thousand remained."
    new "Today, Bagrad was the last vestige of that old empire. A city that once housed millions; now barely a hundred-thousand remained."

    old "And yet, the city still stood. Its vast monuments immune to the forces of nature and decay, testament to a place that once meant something."
    new "And yet, the city still stood. Its vast monuments immune to the forces of nature and decay, testament to a place that once meant something."

    old "The people of Bagrad, and it's royal family, were much like their city."
    new "The people of Bagrad, and it's royal family, were much like their city."

    old "Though time had changed, their perception of themselves seemed immutable. Even now they considered themselves far above the rest of the world, even as the world had all but forgotten about them."
    new "Though time had changed, their perception of themselves seemed immutable. Even now they considered themselves far above the rest of the world, even as the world had all but forgotten about them."

    old "It was this arrogance that had brought Sarah and Xan to the city."
    new "It was this arrogance that had brought Sarah and Xan to the city."

    old "The head of the royal family, the Shah Mahda, had hosted some festivities several months ago."
    new "The head of the royal family, the Shah Mahda, had hosted some festivities several months ago."

    old "During the festivities, a young Mythran prince too drunk on wine, spoke too truthfully of what had become of Bagrad and its people."
    new "During the festivities, a young Mythran prince too drunk on wine, spoke too truthfully of what had become of Bagrad and its people."

    old "The Shah Mahda, too arrogant to let this slight pass, killed the young Mythran prince."
    new "The Shah Mahda, too arrogant to let this slight pass, killed the young Mythran prince."

    old "The Shah had failed to understand that Bagrad survived by virtue of being too unimportant to conquer, but with the spilling of important blood he had given a cause for war that weighed heavier than strategy."
    new "The Shah had failed to understand that Bagrad survived by virtue of being too unimportant to conquer, but with the spilling of important blood he had given a cause for war that weighed heavier than strategy."

    old "A few miles outside of the city walls, a Mythran army led by the uncle of the slain prince was camped. Soon they would begin their assault."
    new "A few miles outside of the city walls, a Mythran army led by the uncle of the slain prince was camped. Soon they would begin their assault."

    old "In desperation, the Shah had reached out to any potential ally who might save him, but a scarce few had answered."
    new "In desperation, the Shah had reached out to any potential ally who might save him, but a scarce few had answered."

    old "That was, until Xan told Sarah that they were going to offer the city their protection."
    new "That was, until Xan told Sarah that they were going to offer the city their protection."

    old "It was not unheard of for mages to step unto a battlefield, but Sarah could not help wonder why this battle was worth their intervention."
    new "It was not unheard of for mages to step unto a battlefield, but Sarah could not help wonder why this battle was worth their intervention."

    old "I doubt they're going to survive for very long."
    new "I doubt they're going to survive for very long."

    old "Xan stood off to the side, his neck craned, seemingly trying to find someone or something."
    new "Xan stood off to the side, his neck craned, seemingly trying to find someone or something."

    old "He seemed distracted."
    new "He seemed distracted."

    old "We'll just need to make sure they make it through today."
    new "We'll just need to make sure they make it through today."

    old "A Mythran host is no joke, but the Bagrad army should be able to keep them off for a while. We're mostly here just to protect the palace from anyone that sneaks past the main battle."
    new "A Mythran host is no joke, but the Bagrad army should be able to keep them off for a while. We're mostly here just to protect the palace from anyone that sneaks past the main battle."

    old "Sarah observed Xan. He was always so different when they left the house. Out here in the real world."
    new "Sarah observed Xan. He was always so different when they left the house. Out here in the real world."

    old "Anxious, seemingly always on edge."
    new "Anxious, seemingly always on edge."

    old "I'm glad my years of magical training can be put to use as a bodyguard."
    new "I'm glad my years of magical training can be put to use as a bodyguard."

    old "Yes, it's not the most glorious task, but sometimes even these base things need to be done."
    new "Yes, it's not the most glorious task, but sometimes even these base things need to be done."

    old "Why does this need to be done?"
    new "Why does this need to be done?"

    old "This city..."
    new "This city..."

    old "It's impressive, sure, and it's full of history, but it's basically the world's most awe-inspiring backwater."
    new "It's impressive, sure, and it's full of history, but it's basically the world's most awe-inspiring backwater."

    old "What do we care if it falls over some party gone foul?"
    new "What do we care if it falls over some party gone foul?"

    old "Xan turned his attention to Sarah."
    new "Xan turned his attention to Sarah."

    old "We don't, not really, but Bagrad and its palace are still home to a hoard of treasures."
    new "We don't, not really, but Bagrad and its palace are still home to a hoard of treasures."

    old "The order had been in contact with the Shah for a long time to negotiate an exchange for some specific items, but he always dragged his feet."
    new "The order had been in contact with the Shah for a long time to negotiate an exchange for some specific items, but he always dragged his feet."

    old "We didn't press the issue because we imagined we had more time, but after he made a mess of it, we're now suddenly very short on time."
    new "We didn't press the issue because we imagined we had more time, but after he made a mess of it, we're now suddenly very short on time."

    old "If we let the Mythran army and its mercenaries into the city, who knows where any of it ends up."
    new "If we let the Mythran army and its mercenaries into the city, who knows where any of it ends up."

    old "So this is all over some treasure?"
    new "So this is all over some treasure?"

    old "It's not the gold or the jewels we care about. There are items in the treasury that are too dangerous to be unaccounted for. Items we can't allow slipping into the wrong hands."
    new "It's not the gold or the jewels we care about. There are items in the treasury that are too dangerous to be unaccounted for. Items we can't allow slipping into the wrong hands."

    old "The Shah is finally desperate enough to give us access to the hoard. All we need to do is keep him and his family safe."
    new "The Shah is finally desperate enough to give us access to the hoard. All we need to do is keep him and his family safe."

    old "Sarah looked around the palace."
    new "Sarah looked around the palace."

    old "It was different in style from where she had grown up, and yet, she could recognize it. The wealth, the opulence."
    new "It was different in style from where she had grown up, and yet, she could recognize it. The wealth, the opulence."

    old "Some things were the same in every culture."
    new "Some things were the same in every culture."

    old "Speaking of our honorable host and his family, where are they?"
    new "Speaking of our honorable host and his family, where are they?"

    old "He promised he would receive us, but you'll come to find he's a...odd man."
    new "He promised he would receive us, but you'll come to find he's a...odd man."

    old "Odder than you?"
    new "Odder than you?"

    old "Maybe even odder than me, yes."
    new "Maybe even odder than me, yes."

    old "He's obsessed with playing these little games to remind everyone of how important he is. Loves to make people wait."
    new "He's obsessed with playing these little games to remind everyone of how important he is. Loves to make people wait."

    old "It can be exhausting, but given the circumstance, best we can do is grin and bear it. We'll get access to the vault soon enough, then we're out of here."
    new "It can be exhausting, but given the circumstance, best we can do is grin and bear it. We'll get access to the vault soon enough, then we're out of here."

    old "Why even bother? Can't we just blast it open."
    new "Why even bother? Can't we just blast it open."

    old "Most likely it has magical protections of its own. And even if we could blow it open, the whole world would hear the story of the two thief mages, and who would trust us after that?"
    new "Most likely it has magical protections of its own. And even if we could blow it open, the whole world would hear the story of the two thief mages, and who would trust us after that?"

    old "Also...more importantly...there is the matter of the vault's location."
    new "Also...more importantly...there is the matter of the vault's location."

    old "Well...I don't actually know where it is."
    new "Well...I don't actually know where it is."

    old "Sarah was surprised to hear this. Xan was often the person who had all the answers."
    new "Sarah was surprised to hear this. Xan was often the person who had all the answers."

    old "You don't know where it is?"
    new "You don't know where it is?"

    old "I know it's here, in the palace, but this place is a nightmare. Endless hallways and secret tunnels. Nobody has any idea where it is, other than the Shah and his most trusted advisors."
    new "I know it's here, in the palace, but this place is a nightmare. Endless hallways and secret tunnels. Nobody has any idea where it is, other than the Shah and his most trusted advisors."

    old "What about the people that build the secret tunnels."
    new "What about the people that build the secret tunnels."

    old "No, they killed those."
    new "No, they killed those."

    old "Sarah wasn't sure if Xan was joking or not."
    new "Sarah wasn't sure if Xan was joking or not."

    old "A silence lingered between the pair, but neither seemed to mind it much."
    new "A silence lingered between the pair, but neither seemed to mind it much."

    old "Sarah watched the edges of the great palace room. Servants scurried around, carrying out their tasks."
    new "Sarah watched the edges of the great palace room. Servants scurried around, carrying out their tasks."

    old "It almost seemed tragic, Sarah realized. This vast throne room was many times larger than the one in Castle Reinmeer, and yet, there were fewer servants here than at home."
    new "It almost seemed tragic, Sarah realized. This vast throne room was many times larger than the one in Castle Reinmeer, and yet, there were fewer servants here than at home."

    old "Its immense size once communicated greatness, but now it seemed only to mock those who remained."
    new "Its immense size once communicated greatness, but now it seemed only to mock those who remained."

    old "Sarah killed the time by studying every inch of the room. Going over it twice, and parts of it thrice, she was finally saved from her boredom when something began to stir on the other end of the room."
    new "Sarah killed the time by studying every inch of the room. Going over it twice, and parts of it thrice, she was finally saved from her boredom when something began to stir on the other end of the room."

    old "A door had been thrown open and a cadre of servants swarmed behind the man who now walked ahead of the pack."
    new "A door had been thrown open and a cadre of servants swarmed behind the man who now walked ahead of the pack."

    old "Sarah had never seen the Shah Mahda before, but she could deduce from the man's posture that he must be the one."
    new "Sarah had never seen the Shah Mahda before, but she could deduce from the man's posture that he must be the one."

    old "All rise!"
    new "All rise!"

    old "You stand in the presence of the avatar of the singular god. Eldest in the line of Bagrad. Shah Mahda!"
    new "You stand in the presence of the avatar of the singular god. Eldest in the line of Bagrad. Shah Mahda!"

    old "Several other servants struck drums to put force to the announcement."
    new "Several other servants struck drums to put force to the announcement."

    old "The Shah sat down in his throne and motioned for Xan and Sarah to come near."
    new "The Shah sat down in his throne and motioned for Xan and Sarah to come near."

    old "Greetings my esteemed guests."
    new "Greetings my esteemed guests."

    old "Xan bowed low and Sarah imitated him, unsure of the customs of this place."
    new "Xan bowed low and Sarah imitated him, unsure of the customs of this place."

    old "Honourable Shah, it is with humility that we received your invitation and with eagerness that we have answered it."
    new "Honourable Shah, it is with humility that we received your invitation and with eagerness that we have answered it."

    old "Xan always struck Sarah as a man of many faces."
    new "Xan always struck Sarah as a man of many faces."

    old "At home he was distant and academic, but out in the world he always managed to fit in wherever he was, whether in some back alley or a royal palace."
    new "At home he was distant and academic, but out in the world he always managed to fit in wherever he was, whether in some back alley or a royal palace."

    old "It made Sarah wonder, which part was the real Xan, if there was any."
    new "It made Sarah wonder, which part was the real Xan, if there was any."

    old "My family has always been loyal allies to your order. We shall receive you and your apprentice with all the hospitalities that are due."
    new "My family has always been loyal allies to your order. We shall receive you and your apprentice with all the hospitalities that are due."

    old "The rooms have already been prepared for each of you, and we will soon have the rooms ready for the others."
    new "The rooms have already been prepared for each of you, and we will soon have the rooms ready for the others."

    old "A charged silence came over the hall."
    new "A charged silence came over the hall."

    old "Sarah eyed Xan, trying to understand what the Shah meant, but Xan seemed equally confused."
    new "Sarah eyed Xan, trying to understand what the Shah meant, but Xan seemed equally confused."

    old "Honourable Shah, forgive me, but which others do you speak of?"
    new "Honourable Shah, forgive me, but which others do you speak of?"

    old "The other members of your order, who else?"
    new "The other members of your order, who else?"

    old "Your council promised their commitment to my cause. Surely, they do not mean to forsake that vow?"
    new "Your council promised their commitment to my cause. Surely, they do not mean to forsake that vow?"

    old "Of course not, great Shah, but we are that commitment. Me and my apprentice."
    new "Of course not, great Shah, but we are that commitment. Me and my apprentice."

    old "Xan waved his hand towards Sarah, as if to reinforce his point."
    new "Xan waved his hand towards Sarah, as if to reinforce his point."

    old "A loud crack rang out through the hall, it's echo carried deep into the palace hallways."
    new "A loud crack rang out through the hall, it's echo carried deep into the palace hallways."

    old "A bowl that had been sat upon the edge of the Shah's throne was send clattering across the stone floor."
    new "A bowl that had been sat upon the edge of the Shah's throne was send clattering across the stone floor."

    old "Lying wretches!"
    new "Lying wretches!"

    old "Sarah watched the Shah's face, now contorted with rage, his eyes wildly jumping between Xan and herself."
    new "Sarah watched the Shah's face, now contorted with rage, his eyes wildly jumping between Xan and herself."

    old "I was promised the support of your order, and all they send is you and this child!?"
    new "I was promised the support of your order, and all they send is you and this child!?"

    old "Xan raised his hand in protest."
    new "Xan raised his hand in protest."

    old "Trust me, Shah Mahda, our order makes right on its promise. Together, the both of us, are each talented mages with years of experience and training."
    new "Trust me, Shah Mahda, our order makes right on its promise. Together, the both of us, are each talented mages with years of experience and training."

    old "My apprentice is this in name only, she is worth a hundred knights, to this I will attest."
    new "My apprentice is this in name only, she is worth a hundred knights, to this I will attest."

    old "We vowed to keep your family safe, and this we will do."
    new "We vowed to keep your family safe, and this we will do."

    old "The Shah stomped the edge of his throne with his fist again."
    new "The Shah stomped the edge of his throne with his fist again."

    old "There is an army at my gate!"
    new "There is an army at my gate!"

    old "I need a hundred mages to burn them and blacken the sky with their ashes, and all I get is you and this miserable girl..."
    new "I need a hundred mages to burn them and blacken the sky with their ashes, and all I get is you and this miserable girl..."

    old "You have betrayed me. If you will not keep your word, I will not keep mine. The vault will remain closed to you."
    new "You have betrayed me. If you will not keep your word, I will not keep mine. The vault will remain closed to you."

    old "Sarah watched Xan's body language shift. This threat appeared to have changed something."
    new "Sarah watched Xan's body language shift. This threat appeared to have changed something."

    old "Honourable Shah..."
    new "Honourable Shah..."

    old "If this is what you wish, tell us now and we will leave by your command."
    new "If this is what you wish, tell us now and we will leave by your command."

    old "Sarah could see the Shah observing them."
    new "Sarah could see the Shah observing them."

    old "But she also realized that Xan had understood the Shah."
    new "But she also realized that Xan had understood the Shah."

    old "The man's threats were empty. His position was already too weak. He could barely afford to miss a single soldier, let alone two mages."
    new "The man's threats were empty. His position was already too weak. He could barely afford to miss a single soldier, let alone two mages."

    old "The Shah gestured with his hand, as if the matter was settled."
    new "The Shah gestured with his hand, as if the matter was settled."

    old "You may stay, for now..."
    new "You may stay, for now..."

    old "But your order will have to answer for this when the fighting is over!"
    new "But your order will have to answer for this when the fighting is over!"

    old "I promise that the elders meant no insult. They will make amends for this...miscommunication."
    new "I promise that the elders meant no insult. They will make amends for this...miscommunication."

    old "The Shah's bluff had been called, but Xan had tactfully allowed him to withdraw with his ego in tact."
    new "The Shah's bluff had been called, but Xan had tactfully allowed him to withdraw with his ego in tact."

    old "Do you see, Samayra? I told you to count your fingers when you're around these creatures."
    new "Do you see, Samayra? I told you to count your fingers when you're around these creatures."

    old "Suddenly, Sarah noticed someone standing off to the side of the Shah, hidden away in the shadow of his throne."
    new "Suddenly, Sarah noticed someone standing off to the side of the Shah, hidden away in the shadow of his throne."

    old "Yes, father."
    new "Yes, father."

    old "Her voice carried softly through the room."
    new "Her voice carried softly through the room."

    old "She kept her head down, eyes fixed to the floor. There was something about her, quiet in both voice and presence."
    new "She kept her head down, eyes fixed to the floor. There was something about her, quiet in both voice and presence."

    old "Sarah studied the girl. She was close to herself in age but she gave off a quiet and reserved energy that made her seem so much younger."
    new "Sarah studied the girl. She was close to herself in age but she gave off a quiet and reserved energy that made her seem so much younger."

    old "Or perhaps, Sarah considered, it was she herself who had become older than her age over these last few years."
    new "Or perhaps, Sarah considered, it was she herself who had become older than her age over these last few years."

    old "The Shah had spoken to his daugther, but paid her little heed after, turning his attention back to Xan."
    new "The Shah had spoken to his daugther, but paid her little heed after, turning his attention back to Xan."

    old "My war council will soon gather to discuss our strategy in defending the city. I insist that you join us."
    new "My war council will soon gather to discuss our strategy in defending the city. I insist that you join us."

    old "Xan bowed low again."
    new "Xan bowed low again."

    old "It would be a great honour for both of us."
    new "It would be a great honour for both of us."

    old "The Shah shook his head."
    new "The Shah shook his head."

    old "Only you. The girl can learn what she needs after the council. I won't have some apprentice sitting in."
    new "Only you. The girl can learn what she needs after the council. I won't have some apprentice sitting in."

    old "With the wave of his hand, the Shah dismissed the both of them. Advisors flocked to his seat, hoping to spare a moment with him, but Sarah could see he was distracted."
    new "With the wave of his hand, the Shah dismissed the both of them. Advisors flocked to his seat, hoping to spare a moment with him, but Sarah could see he was distracted."

    old "Sarah tried to imagine if Thomas had been like this..."
    new "Sarah tried to imagine if Thomas had been like this..."

    old "When the tribesmen invaded, and he had been left all alone to defend Rosanna, did he have these quiet moments of fear?"
    new "When the tribesmen invaded, and he had been left all alone to defend Rosanna, did he have these quiet moments of fear?"

    old "Sarah shook her head to clear it, as she walked along with Xan to the far side of the room."
    new "Sarah shook her head to clear it, as she walked along with Xan to the far side of the room."

    old "Thinking about her brother was too painful, and yet, even years later she still found herself thinking about him."
    new "Thinking about her brother was too painful, and yet, even years later she still found herself thinking about him."

    old "One part of her wanted to numb the pain, the other wanted it to linger forever like a poorly healed wound so that she might never forget him."
    new "One part of her wanted to numb the pain, the other wanted it to linger forever like a poorly healed wound so that she might never forget him."

    old "Well, that went better than I thought it would."
    new "Well, that went better than I thought it would."

    old "You weren't surprised that he was angry that it's just you and me?"
    new "You weren't surprised that he was angry that it's just you and me?"

    old "I know the council played coy with their promises, but I also knew he had no choice but to accept our help."
    new "I know the council played coy with their promises, but I also knew he had no choice but to accept our help."

    old "Will the two of us be enough to make a difference?"
    new "Will the two of us be enough to make a difference?"

    old "Xan stared into the distance."
    new "Xan stared into the distance."

    old "Maybe, it depends on how the fighting plays out. But it doesn't matter."
    new "Maybe, it depends on how the fighting plays out. But it doesn't matter."

    old "It doesn't?"
    new "It doesn't?"

    old "No, we're not here to save Bagrad. Whether it survives or falls is irrelevant. The vault remains the first priority."
    new "No, we're not here to save Bagrad. Whether it survives or falls is irrelevant. The vault remains the first priority."

    old "But if Bagrad falls and the palace is overrun with soldiers and mercenaries, I imagine finding the vault would prove difficult."
    new "But if Bagrad falls and the palace is overrun with soldiers and mercenaries, I imagine finding the vault would prove difficult."

    old "Correct, so we should at least try to keep them out for a few days. Enough time for the Shah to let us into the vault, or otherwise find a way in."
    new "Correct, so we should at least try to keep them out for a few days. Enough time for the Shah to let us into the vault, or otherwise find a way in."

    old "Xan suddenly turned towards Sarah."
    new "Xan suddenly turned towards Sarah."

    old "Speaking of that, you need to get friendly with the Shah's daughter."
    new "Speaking of that, you need to get friendly with the Shah's daughter."

    old "I'm not really looking for new friends at the moment."
    new "I'm not really looking for new friends at the moment."

    old "Xan flashed a pained grin."
    new "Xan flashed a pained grin."

    old "She's the Shah's daughter. Outside of the Shah himself, there might not be anyone who knows as much about this palace."
    new "She's the Shah's daughter. Outside of the Shah himself, there might not be anyone who knows as much about this palace."

    old "If anyone has an idea as to where the vault might be, it's her. And if the Shah tries to hold out on his end of the deal, we might need to use her."
    new "If anyone has an idea as to where the vault might be, it's her. And if the Shah tries to hold out on his end of the deal, we might need to use her."

    old "And you think she's going to help us?"
    new "And you think she's going to help us?"

    old "If you befriend her, she just might."
    new "If you befriend her, she just might."

    old "And talk to her about what?"
    new "And talk to her about what?"

    old "Xan threw up his hands."
    new "Xan threw up his hands."

    old "You're both princesses, that's a start."
    new "You're both princesses, that's a start."

    old "I haven't been one for a long time now."
    new "I haven't been one for a long time now."

    old "You'll be surprised how fast it comes back to you. I'm going to attend the war council. During the council, the Shah will be seperated from his daughter, that's when you can make your move."
    new "You'll be surprised how fast it comes back to you. I'm going to attend the war council. During the council, the Shah will be seperated from his daughter, that's when you can make your move."

    old "Sarah looked across the hall."
    new "Sarah looked across the hall."

    old "In the shadow of her father's throne, she could see the thin frame of the girl. So small and unimposing, Sarah imagined she might just fade away."
    new "In the shadow of her father's throne, she could see the thin frame of the girl. So small and unimposing, Sarah imagined she might just fade away."

    old "Samayra, that's what her father had called her. Sarah liked the name."
    new "Samayra, that's what her father had called her. Sarah liked the name."

